Overview

This repository contains the complete implementation of a Hybrid XGBoostâ€“LSTM framework for predicting traffic accident risk under adverse weather and dynamic traffic conditions.
The model combines:

XGBoost (Stage 1) for learning complex nonlinear relations between traffic + weather features and crash likelihood, and

LSTM (Stage 2) for capturing temporal dependencies across recent time intervals using the XGBoost risk score sequence.

This hybrid design enhances early-warning capabilities for traffic-safety and Intelligent Transportation System (ITS) applications.
